FBIS4-37264 "drnes118_j_94035" FBIS-NES-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Aden Reports Attacks by North, Southern Successes Aden Reports Attacks by North, Southern Successes Aden Says Northern Attacks Continue EA1806191494 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1630 GMT 18 Jun 94 EA1806191494 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1630 GMT 18 Jun 94 Arabic BFN [Statement issued by "a responsible source at the Presidential Council"; place and date not given] [Text] Despite the appeals of the world to the rulers of Sanaa to cease fire and to stop the shelling of vital economic installations and residential quarters, the Sanaa regime continued throughout today its shelling and barbarous acts and (?initiated) attacks on all front at about 1730 this evening. Our brave Armed Forces, as well as volunteers from the sons of our steadfast people, are repulsing them. We announce to the world our legitimate right to defend our territory and the honor of our womenfolk since the Sanaa regime does not respect any laws or values. Our Armed Forces, with God's will and assistance and in cooperation with the sons of our people, will repulse the attacks of the aggressors and will protect dauntless Aden. These barbarous attacks will only increase the steadfastness of the sons of our people in Aden and their challenge of the aggressors.
